		<td><b>28pin 1 or 2 meg eproms?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Anyone know if they even exist? Looking for 1 or 2 meg 28 pin eproms.  Thanks!
<br />
<br />(well I know NES game's used some, so some exist somewhere, just dont know where)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Great Hierophant</b> [ Sun Sep 11, 2005 2:31 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NES games did use 128 Kilobyte (1 Megabit) 28-pin Program ROMs at times, but they are not common by any means.  No NES game ever used a 256 Kilobyte (2 Megabyte) 28-pin ROM.  I assume Nintendo used these odd ROMs during chip shortages or when they could get a good deal on them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


